Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> The dICO app was used by Utrum to carry out an atomic-swap powered decentralized ICO

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> however, the app needs some improvements along with marketmaker

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> our plan was to develop an improved version of the dico app to offer an easy to use dICO app for our clients. Not only for KICs but for ETH assets, Nem assets, and any other coin you can trade on BarterDEX protocol

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> The advantages of a dICO is that you are fulfilling the orders atomically. There is no trust involved which is gamechanging for ICOs. Contributors usually have to trust that the ICO issuer will pay the tokens.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> definitely. The more tools we have out our disposal the more things we can offer our clients.
